&lt;p&gt;A handheld game console programmable with (Micro/Circuit)Python.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="project-thumb"&gt;
&lt;a class="reference external image-reference" href="/_images/4787691512171711474.jpg"&gt;&lt;img alt="projects/project-27629/images/4787691512171711474.jpg" src="projects/project-27629/images/4787691512171711474.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a class="reference external image-reference" href="/_images/5532001510259340085.jpg"&gt;&lt;img alt="projects/project-27629/images/5532001510259340085.jpg" src="projects/project-27629/images/5532001510259340085.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a class="reference external image-reference" href="/_images/5854921525097630407.jpg"&gt;&lt;img alt="projects/project-27629/images/5854921525097630407.jpg" src="projects/project-27629/images/5854921525097630407.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a class="reference external image-reference" href="/_images/9011701528149736254.jpg"&gt;&lt;img alt="projects/project-27629/images/9011701528149736254.jpg" src="projects/project-27629/images/9011701528149736254.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a class="reference external image-reference" href="/_images/8563941525097646527.jpg"&gt;&lt;img alt="projects/project-27629/images/8563941525097646527.jpg" src="projects/project-27629/images/8563941525097646527.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a class="reference external image-reference" href="/_images/8201321527494944003.jpg"&gt;&lt;img alt="projects/project-27629/images/8201321527494944003.jpg" src="projects/project-27629/images/8201321527494944003.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight-none notranslate"&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;A small game console directly programmable in Python. I always wanted
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;to make this, and after my work on &lt;a class="reference internal" href="../../../projects/project-21578/#project-21578"&gt;&lt;span class="std std-ref"&gt;PewPew FeatherWing&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; I finally decided that I’m ready.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The first version may be a bit of a stretch — I tried to make it as
small as possible, fitting in the 5x5cm limit of PCB manufacturers, so
that it will be cheap to make the PCBs. Using the cheap ST7735 TFT
display, and a cheap ATSAMD21E chip. I also tried to put all the
components on one side of the board.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Of course the hard part is writing a game library, and the actual
games. There is already one simple platformer game written as a demo,
and the software library is getting new features added as needed.&lt;/p&gt;
